  "_readme": "Tier-1 procedural + Tier-2 real CC0 models. Monster entries point at Quaternius Ultimate Monsters glTF (CC0, self-contained, animated: Idle/Walk/Run/HitReact/Death/Jump). Hero/skeleton entries point at KayKit Adventurers/Skeletons GLBs (CC0): the character mesh has zero embedded animations, so `animSource` supplies the shared 'Rig_Medium' rig GLBs (General = Idle/Hit/Death/Throw/Use_Item, MovementBasic = Walking/Running) whose clips are merged in and bound by shared bone names. anims maps game states -> glTF clip names. Wolf/wraith/golem stay procedural. Village/dungeon/field static props point at KayKit Medieval Hexagon Pack (buildings/blue + neutral fence + decoration nature/props) and KayKit Dungeon Remastered (pillar, torch_lit) glTF, all CC0, no anims needed. See ASSETS.md. `faceOffset` (radians): all KayKit/Quaternius unit models are set to 1.5708 (Pi/2) as a first-guess correction for the capsule-vs-GLB forward-axis mismatch (units.ts does `rotation.y = -facing + faceOffset`; the procedural capsule faces +X at offset 0, these GLBs are assumed to face +Z). If a model ends up facing directly opposite its travel direction after a browser check, flip it by Pi (i.e. -1.5708 or 4.7124); if it's off 90 degrees the other way, use -1.5708 instead.",

